stnIpRouting.name: stnIpRouting
stnIpRouting.contactinfo: Spring Tide Networks, Inc. Customer Service Postal: 3 Clock Tower Place Maynard, MA 01754 Tel: 1 888-786-4357 Email: stncs@springtidenet.com
stnIpRouting.description: This MIB module describes managed objects of the IP Routing subsystems that are proprietary to Spring Tide Networks.

stnIpRtCacheEntries.name: stnIpRtCacheEntries
stnIpRtCacheEntries.description: The number of current cache entries.

stnIpRtCacheMisses.name: stnIpRtCacheMisses
stnIpRtCacheMisses.description: The number of failed attempts to locate an IP address in the route cache.

stnIpRtCacheHits.name: stnIpRtCacheHits
stnIpRtCacheHits.description: The number of successful attempts to locate an IP address in the route cache.

stnIpRtCacheRemovals.name: stnIpRtCacheRemovals
stnIpRtCacheRemovals.description: The number of times an entry has been removed as a result of the need to insert an entry into a full table.

stnIpRoutingCacheTable.name: stnIpRoutingCacheTable
stnIpRoutingCacheTable.description: Table of IP routing cache entries.

stnIpRtCacheIpAddress.name: stnIpRtCacheIpAddress
stnIpRtCacheIpAddress.description: The destination IP address of this route.

stnIpRtCacheIpMask.name: stnIpRtCacheIpMask
stnIpRtCacheIpMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the ipCidrRouteDest field.

stnIpRtCacheNextHop.name: stnIpRtCacheNextHop
stnIpRtCacheNextHop.description: On remote routes, the address of the next sys- tem en route; Otherwise, 0.0.0.0.

stnIpRtCacheIfIndex.name: stnIpRtCacheIfIndex
stnIpRtCacheIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value which identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached

stnIpRtCacheRouteType.name: stnIpRtCacheRouteType
stnIpRtCacheRouteType.description: The type of route as described in RFC 2096

stnIpRtCacheStatus.name: stnIpRtCacheStatus
stnIpRtCacheStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

stnIpCircExtIfIndex.name: stnIpCircExtIfIndex
stnIpCircExtIfIndex.description: An index value which uniquely identifies the local physical interface which this circuit uses. This value identifies the same interface identified by ifIndex in MIB-2.

stnIpCircExtAdminState.name: stnIpCircExtAdminState
stnIpCircExtAdminState.description: Enable or disable the operation of IP on the specified interface.

stnIpCircExtOperState.name: stnIpCircExtOperState
stnIpCircExtOperState.description: The operational state of the circuit. May or may not be the same as administrative state.

stnIpCircExtIpAddress.name: stnIpCircExtIpAddress
stnIpCircExtIpAddress.description: The IP address of the interface. For unnumbered interfaces this will be 0.0.0.0.

stnIpCircExtIpMask.name: stnIpCircExtIpMask
stnIpCircExtIpMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

stnIpCircExtMaxReasm.name: stnIpCircExtMaxReasm
stnIpCircExtMaxReasm.description: The size of the largest IP datagram which this entity can re-assemble from incoming IP fragmented datagrams received on this interface.

stnIpCircExtMaxMtu.name: stnIpCircExtMaxMtu
stnIpCircExtMaxMtu.description: The size of the largest datagram which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets. For interfaces that are used for transmitting network datagrams, this is the size of the largest network datagram that can be sent on the interface.

stnIpCircExtBcastAddr.name: stnIpCircExtBcastAddr
stnIpCircExtBcastAddr.description: The value of the least-significant bit in the IP broadcast address used for sending datagrams on the (logical) interface associated with the IP address of this entry. For example, when the Internet standard all-ones broadcast address is used, the value will be 1. This value applies to both the subnet and network broadcasts addresses used by the entity on this (logical) interface.

stnIpDetailsTable.name: stnIpDetailsTable
stnIpDetailsTable.description: This table provides additional information about failed ip messages and icmp messages. When the table reaches its maximum size and a new entry needs to be added, the entire table will be cleared.

stnIpDetailsEntry.name: stnIpDetailsEntry
stnIpDetailsEntry.description: An entry within the STN IP Details Table.

stnIpDetailsIndex.name: stnIpDetailsIndex
stnIpDetailsIndex.description: A unique index for this table.

stnIpDetailsSource.name: stnIpDetailsSource
stnIpDetailsSource.description: The source address within the packet.

stnIpDetailsDest.name: stnIpDetailsDest
stnIpDetailsDest.description: The destination address within the packet.

stnIpDetailsType.name: stnIpDetailsType
stnIpDetailsType.description: Indicates either an IP address or header error, or ICMP problem message.

stnIpDetailsTimeStamp.name: stnIpDetailsTimeStamp
stnIpDetailsTimeStamp.description: Value of sysUpTime when this entry was added.

stnIpDetailsHeader.name: stnIpDetailsHeader
stnIpDetailsHeader.description: IP header of this error packet.

stnIpMaxRoutingTableSize.name: stnIpMaxRoutingTableSize
stnIpMaxRoutingTableSize.description: Maximum size of the ip routing table.

stnIpCurrentRoutingTableSize.name: stnIpCurrentRoutingTableSize
stnIpCurrentRoutingTableSize.description: Current size of the ip routing table.

stnIpRouterRouteLimitExceeded.name: stnIpRouterRouteLimitExceeded
stnIpRouterRouteLimitExceeded.description: A stnIpRouterRouteLimitExceeded signifies that a route add operation failed due to reaching maximum number of routes in the routing table as specified by the stnIpMaxRoutingTableSize variable.

stnIpEngineRouteLimitExceeded.name: stnIpEngineRouteLimitExceeded
stnIpEngineRouteLimitExceeded.description: A stnIpEngineRouteLimitExceeded signifies that a route add operation failed due to reaching maximum number of routes on the router's engine as specified by the stnCpuIpRouteLimit variable.

stnArpExtTtl.name: stnArpExtTtl
stnArpExtTtl.description: The lifetime of an ARP entry within the router.

stnArpExtRcvdRequests.name: stnArpExtRcvdRequests
stnArpExtRcvdRequests.description: The number of ARP received requests within the router.

stnArpExtRcvdReplies.name: stnArpExtRcvdReplies
stnArpExtRcvdReplies.description: The number of ARP received replies within the router.

stnArpExtSendRequests.name: stnArpExtSendRequests
stnArpExtSendRequests.description: The number of ARP send requests within the router.

stnArpExtSendReplies.name: stnArpExtSendReplies
stnArpExtSendReplies.description: The number of ARP send replies within the router.

stnArpCircExtIfIndex.name: stnArpCircExtIfIndex
stnArpCircExtIfIndex.description: An index value which uniquely identifies the local physical interface which this circuit uses. This value identifies the same interface identified by ifIndex in MIB-2.

stnArpCircExtDoProxy.name: stnArpCircExtDoProxy
stnArpCircExtDoProxy.description: Enable or disable ARP proxy responses on the specified interface.

stnArpCircExtDoResp.name: stnArpCircExtDoResp
stnArpCircExtDoResp.description: Enable or disable the sending of ARP responses on specified circuit.

stnArpCircExtWanProxy.name: stnArpCircExtWanProxy
stnArpCircExtWanProxy.description: Enable or disable ARP WAN proxy responses on the specified interface.

stnRipExtAdminState.name: stnRipExtAdminState
stnRipExtAdminState.description: Enable or disable the operation of RIP on all interfaces.

stnRipExtUpdateTime.name: stnRipExtUpdateTime
stnRipExtUpdateTime.description: The time between transmission of RIP updates.

stnRipCircExtIfIndex.name: stnRipCircExtIfIndex
stnRipCircExtIfIndex.description: An index value which uniquely identifies the local physical interface which this circuit uses. This value identifies the same interface identified by ifIndex in MIB-2.

stnRipCircExtTalk.name: stnRipCircExtTalk
stnRipCircExtTalk.description: Enable or disable RIP transmission on the specified interface.

stnRipCircExtListen.name: stnRipCircExtListen
stnRipCircExtListen.description: Enable or disable RIP reception on the specified interface.

stnRipCircExtPoison.name: stnRipCircExtPoison
stnRipCircExtPoison.description: Enable or disable operation of poison reverse on the specified interface. If poison is disabled, split-horizon operation is enabled.
